				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Help for a new bard<a name="46492"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 16 04 6:24 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> Hello, I just recently started a character on the AB server (my original character is a 63 cleric on Aro). I decided on a bard because I was intrigued by the class itself, and then decided on a different server so that I would not be tempted to &quot;twink&quot; this character. Anyway, I have managed to level up to 12 so far, and finished the quests that my guildmaster has given to me. I have my armor (songweavers from Freeport), and I just completed the quest for the sword (orc chief warbeads). 
<br />
~~First off, are there any other armor quests that can be done for upgrades (lets call them newb) past the songweavers armor?
<br />
~~And second, I am still hunting in EC, which is giving me somewhat good xp, but is there a better place that I can go that will help me learn to play the class? (I have done crushbone, Pc, all the xp camps with my cleric so I am not interested in visiting those places again). I really want a place that will let me solo while gaining good xp (I am not looking for a quick level, rather a good learning experience). 
<br />
~~Last, I have looked at the links that are here, read everything that was there, but I am still confused about some things. Mainly, the art of twisting songs and the usuage of instruments. Both have left me extrememly  confused. I would imagine that the art of twisting comes more with practice than anything else, but I am missing the basics somewhere in all the posts that I have read. And instruments, well, I am completly in the dark. If we have a weapon, and if we do not need to purchase and instrument to gain skill (wind, percussion,etc), then why do we need to buy instruments at all? 
<br />
 I would really appreciate any help that can be given to me ...as I said, I am not looking to quickly level this character, I would rather take the time to learn how to play it correctly. <img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-10.gif" border="0" alt="Blushing" hspace="2" /></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
