<br />

<br />
Well, I don't want to start a heated argument based on the merits of soloing and grouping. I am not technically a newb, been playing EQ since beta, BUT, this is the first time I have tried to play a bard (so, in my mind, that makes me a newb, lol). I know the merits of grouping, and the invaluable experience one can gain from doing so, I also know the merits of soloing and that it is one of the best ways to discover what your character is capable of. So, that said, lol, let me try and clarify what I was asking. ~~Is there a place that is recomended to &quot;practice&quot; soloing for those times you don't want to be in a group~~that's the best way I can put it, I guess. 
<br />

<br />
<i>~~The next step up from Songweaver's armor is Lambent~~</i>
<br />

<br />
I have seen the stats and what is needed for this armor, I would have to agree with you that it is not really worth questing for<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-6.gif" border="0" alt="Sad" hspace="2" />...Has anyone gotten the armor that is bought through points in LDoN? And if so, is it worth the points that you have to spend?
