				<td colspan="2"><span>I spent most of my early bard life in Kurn's Tower.  It's good for soloing or grouping.  I mostly grouped though.   At about 14, I went to the Hollowshade area of Paladural.  Easy to get one or two pulls from the beetle looking things there.  Then I went to the Shadowhaven side of Paladural until 21.  It was about this time I went to Lake of Ill Omen and started AEing the sarnack fort and goblin ruins.  This was great experience (about 20%-30% a pull) and I stayed there off and on until about 30 doing some grouping in OT when I got tired of soloing.  
<br />

<br />
As far as grouping and soloing, I switch between them both.  I do a LFA then solo until I find someone looking for a bard my level.  Once you get mid 30s, people will find you for LDONs.  I've managed to keep all my skills maxed following this strategy.
<br />

<br />
I'm Elfvus Questley on Ayonea Ro.  Send me a tell if you have any questions.</span></td>
