			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Help for a new bard<a name="46539"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 16 04 11:43 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Cht`Thk Swarmers drop both.  I camped these instruments when I was around lvl 12 or 13, EXP was good too.  And While going for the Flawless Ivory Horn drop I managed to get about 12 Ivor Horns, all of which sold pretty fast in the bazaar for about 50pp each.
<br />

<br />
As for Lute, and Drum, the Combine ones are really hard to beat for a non-twink Bard.
<br />

<br />
As for Armors, You'll be lvl 50 before you can manage a full suit of ANY of the LDoN armors hehe.  The prices on the low level versions are ridiculous.  Look in the Bazaar for some low level gear that isn't overpriced (recommended level items are good, they grow with you.), get a general idea of the price, and start Farming trash drops for plat.  I farmed stacks of droppables from lvl 1, by the time I was lvl 10 I had well over 700pp in the Bank simply because I looted and vendor sold everything That could stack, by the time I filled up 3 or 4 backpacks full of gear it was time to visit the trainer again anyway.
<br />

<br />
Don't really go to Paludal.  No cash at all drops there unless you get a Bandit group, then you have to deal with mr ninja looter.  Not worth the hassle to me.  Just keep doing what you are doing.
<br />

<br />
At this level do alot of melee soloing if you are gonna solo.  As soon as you get your first Slow/Snare song, you can twist it with Haste, and regen, and you should do fine.  Don't want to let your defense skill get behind.  You can also practice Lull pulling and general puller skills etc.
<br />

<br />

<br />
Going into Kurns Tower would be great for you, try to get in a group, or solo the first floor till you outgrow it.  Once you are confident enough in your abilities you can start working your way down to the Ikky Berserkers Club Camp, and get yourself a not too shabby weapon that tends to sell for a couple k in the bazaar, along with some terrific EXP.  There are also some minor gear items that drop down there occasionally that you might can use.
<br />

<br />
Once you outgrow Kurns you can head over to the Estate of Unrest, and solo inside the building, there you can get some very good pulling/lull practice, and deffinately get your defense up.  But groups prefered inside unless you are decently geared.  A good healer along with you would make it nice though.
<br />

<br />
By the time you leave here you should be at a minimum of lvl 28 or 29 if you stayed in the right areas.  Then head over to highkeep a couple levels.  Once you ding 32/33ish follow your little hearts desire.
<br />

<br />
As far as working instrument skills if you can leave your computer on all night, the best way to get em up is go to PoK before you log equip an instrument, play the appropriate song to raide skill, turn off your monitor, and go to sleep, you'll wake up with Max skill most of the time.  I also do this with swimming<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-2.gif" border="0" alt="Big Smile" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
Anything else you might need to know right now has already been covered.
<br />
</span></td>
