				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Help for a new bard<a name="46841"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 18 04 8:07 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ever since they started putting a number on instrument descriptions indicating the modifier, non-bards are starting to figure out what instruments are good.  However, there are two very common LDoN drop instruments that are worth looking for in bazaar:
<br />

<br />
Trueborn Drum of Dark Rites, Primary, 2.4 mod
<br />
Bloodstained Flute, Primary, 2.2 mod
<br />

<br />
Swapping instruments into your Primary slot is MUCH easier than secondary (one click instead of three).
<br />

<br />
A Primary Lute is the toughee though.  If you can convince people to do Guk LDoNs, there is a cheap 1.8 Primary Lute you can get there with points.  (A REAL nice 2.6 mod Primary Lute in Rajukan, hehe... 570 points though)
<br />

<br />
For armor, you might consider having someone make you some Gothic Steel Armor.  It is blacksmithed, and trivials somewere around 170-200.  If you do LDoNs, forage as much as you can.  Each of the LDoN smithed armors require a foraged component for the tempers.  These can be bargaining tools with the person making your stuff.
<br />

<br />
People also do those LDoN armors for skillups.  Dumpster Dive (check the vendors) at the PoK forges, and see if people have dumped off their LDoN skillup pieces there.  I don't recall the prices the vendors give you, but I think they aren't as silly as what vendors want for fine steel etc.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=564823">Scherzo Glissando </a><BR>
Maestro, Molto Espressivo</span></td>
